This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it presents a tool for searching and organizing legal data. The use of machine learning techniques such as Doc2Vec, link mining, and named entity recognition also suggests that it could belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques such as Doc2Vec suggests that it could belong to the Deep Learning (cs.DL) category. Finally, the focus on legal and constitutional data in developing countries suggests that it could belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) category as well.
